rect.title: A photon is a discrete packet / quantum of energy of an electromagnetic radiation with energy hf.
Photoelectric effect is the emission of electrons (photoelectrons) from a metal surface when electromagnetic radiation of sufficiently high frequency is incident on it.
Work function of the metal: minimum amount of energy required to free an electron from the metal (due to the binding forces exerted on it by the surrounding nuclei).
Wave-particle duality refers to the idea that light and matter (such as electrons) have both wave and particle properties.

Line spectra are produced by isolated atoms, (i.e. atoms which are so far apart that they are not interacting with each other). Each line on the spectrum is for a particular frequency or wavelength of the light incident on the slit.
The absorption line spectrum is a continuous spectrum (a rainbow) crossed by dark lines due to some missing frequencies.

If the sufficiently energetic electron knock an electron out of an inner shell, another electron (within the metal) that exists at a higher energy level will then drop down to fill the vacancy. This transition causes an x-ray photon to be emitted.

If a measurement of position of a particle is made with precision x and a simultaneous measurement of its momentum in the x direction is made with precision p, the product of these 2 uncertainties can never be smaller than h.
